==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fulmar
<hw>Ful"mar</hw> <pr>(f⟦ucr⟧lm⟦aum⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Icel.
<ets>f⟦umac⟧lm⟦amac⟧r</ets>. See <er>foul</er>, and <er>Man</er> a
gull.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of several species of sea
birds, of the family <fam>Procellariid⟦ae⟧</fam>, allied to the
albatrosses and petrels. Among the well-known species are the
<stype>arctic fulmar</stype> (<spn>Fulmarus glacialis</spn>) (called
also <stype>fulmar petrel</stype>, <stype>malduck</stype>, and
<stype>mollemock</stype>), and the giant fulmar (<spn>Ossifraga
gigantea</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fulmarus</ent>⟦br⟧
